main event: An object was observed in the sky over Reynoldsville, Pennsylvania, on June 29, 1963.
interesting points: The object appeared as a bright spot-shaped light and was believed to be over a mile away,It moved laterally in a northerly direction before disappearing over trees,The sighting occurred at 2240L, although the length of observation was not reported,The preliminary conclusions classify the object as a balloon, aircraft, or astronomical phenomenon,The report is part of Project Blue Book documentation.
witness description: The witness described seeing a shepherd egg-shaped object hovering at treetop level, which glowed from within.
